acSystem.name: acSystem

revisions.description: Draft engineering version. Not for release.

acSystem.description: Appian Communications Services MIB definitions file containing configuration and statistics control for system related services. These services include Configuration Management, Event Logging, Statistics Collection, Alarms and Thresholds configuration, OSAP discovery and topology protocol.

AcAccessRights.name: AcAccessRights
AcAccessRights.description: Community access rights: - readOnly: allows read access to all MIB tables with the exception of acCommMgrCommTable and acCommMgrSourceAddrTable. - readWrite: if there are no configured communities with security access rights, it allows read and write access to all MIB tables. However, if there is a security community configured, a community with readWrite access rights will not have read access to acCommMgrCommTable and acCommMgrSourceAddrTable, and it will not have write access to acCommMgrCommTable, acCommMgrSourceAddrTable, acTrapMgrDestAddrTable and acTrapMgrFilterTable. - security allows read-write access to all MIB tables.

acCommMgrCommTable.name: acCommMgrCommTable
acCommMgrCommTable.description: Table for configuring community strings and community access rights.

acCommMgrCommNodeId.name: acCommMgrCommNodeId
acCommMgrCommNodeId.description: Unique identification number of this node within an Appian ring.

acCommMgrCommId.name: acCommMgrCommId
acCommMgrCommId.description: Number that uniquely identifies a community.

acCommMgrCommAdminStatus.name: acCommMgrCommAdminStatus
acCommMgrCommAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acCommMgrCommString.name: acCommMgrCommString
acCommMgrCommString.description: String that uniquely identifies a community.

acCommMgrCommAccessRights.name: acCommMgrCommAccessRights
acCommMgrCommAccessRights.description: Community access rights. See AcAccessRights for the semantics.

acCommMgrSourceAddrTable.name: acCommMgrSourceAddrTable
acCommMgrSourceAddrTable.description: Table that specifies valid SNMP request source IP addresses and/or subnets for the different communities.

acCommMgrSourceAddrEntry.name: acCommMgrSourceAddrEntry
acCommMgrSourceAddrEntry.description: Entry that specifies a valid SNMP request source IP address or subnet for a given community.

acCommMgrSourceAddrNodeId.name: acCommMgrSourceAddrNodeId
acCommMgrSourceAddrNodeId.description: Unique identification number of this node within an Appian ring.

acCommMgrSourceAddrCommId.name: acCommMgrSourceAddrCommId
acCommMgrSourceAddrCommId.description: Number that uniquely identifies a community.

acCommMgrSourceAddrIpAddress.name: acCommMgrSourceAddrIpAddress
acCommMgrSourceAddrIpAddress.description: Valid source IP address for SNMP requests of this community. All source IP addresses are valid for a given community if there are no entries in acCommMgrSourceAddrTable for this community with acCommMgrSourceAddrAdminStatus equal to activate

acCommMgrSourceAddrIpSubnet.name: acCommMgrSourceAddrIpSubnet
acCommMgrSourceAddrIpSubnet.description: Subnet mask for valid source IP subnet for SNMP requests of this community.

acCommMgrSourceAddrAdminStatus.name: acCommMgrSourceAddrAdminStatus
acCommMgrSourceAddrAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acStatsMgrTable.name: acStatsMgrTable
acStatsMgrTable.description: A table of statistics manager configuration parameters which is indexed by AcNodeId.

acStatsMgrEntry.name: acStatsMgrEntry
acStatsMgrEntry.description: The configuration and status parameters controlling the Statistics Manager service on this specific node.

acStatsMgrNodeId.name: acStatsMgrNodeId
acStatsMgrNodeId.description: The unique node identification number assigned by the EMS system to uniquely identify this node within an Appian ring of OSAP's.

acStatsMgrAdminStatus.name: acStatsMgrAdminStatus
acStatsMgrAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acEventMgrControlTable.name: acEventMgrControlTable
acEventMgrControlTable.description: A table of configuration parameters controlling the event manager. The event manager is responsible for logging security and application state changes generated on a node. These events are stored in non-volitile memory and may be sent as traps to the EMS system.

acEventMgrControlEntry.name: acEventMgrControlEntry
acEventMgrControlEntry.description: The configuration and status parameters controlling the Event Logging Manager service on this specific node.

acEventMgrControlNodeId.name: acEventMgrControlNodeId
acEventMgrControlNodeId.description: The unique node identification number assigned by the EMS system to uniquely identify this node within an Appian ring of OSAP's.

acEventMgrControlAdminStatus.name: acEventMgrControlAdminStatus
acEventMgrControlAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acEventMgrControlLogMode.name: acEventMgrControlLogMode
acEventMgrControlLogMode.description: There are two kinds of logs in OSAP: regular log, and security log. This is the attribute to control the mode of operation of the regular event log. The regular event log can be configured to write to flash, or it can be disabled. When disabled, the event manager will keep a record of events in memory, which are available to the local CLI/TL1 but are not persistant.

acEventMgrControlLogMaxFileSize.name: acEventMgrControlLogMaxFileSize
acEventMgrControlLogMaxFileSize.description: The size of the regular event log on the file system measured in k-bytes.

acEventMgrControlLogCurrentSize.name: acEventMgrControlLogCurrentSize
acEventMgrControlLogCurrentSize.description: The current size of the regular event log measured in k-bytes.

acEventMgrControlLogFileName.name: acEventMgrControlLogFileName
acEventMgrControlLogFileName.description: The name of the binary regular log file.

acEventMgrControlLogFileWrapEnable.name: acEventMgrControlLogFileWrapEnable
acEventMgrControlLogFileWrapEnable.description: When set to true, tells the event log manager to wrap the regular event log file when it has reached the maximum size. Oldest log entries are overwritten first when a wrap condition is reached.

acEventMgrControlSecurityLogMode.name: acEventMgrControlSecurityLogMode
acEventMgrControlSecurityLogMode.description: There are two kinds of logs in OSAP: regular log, and security log. This is the attribute to control the mode of operation of the security event log. The security event log can be configured to write to flash, or it can be disabled. When disabled, the event manager will keep a record of events in memory, which are available to the local CLI/TL1 but are not persistant.

acEventMgrControlSecurityLogMaxFileSize.name: acEventMgrControlSecurityLogMaxFileSize
acEventMgrControlSecurityLogMaxFileSize.description: The size of the regular security log on the file system measured in k-bytes.

acEventMgrControlSecurityLogCurrentSize.name: acEventMgrControlSecurityLogCurrentSize
acEventMgrControlSecurityLogCurrentSize.description: The current size of the security event log measured in k-bytes.

acEventMgrControlSecurityLogFileName.name: acEventMgrControlSecurityLogFileName
acEventMgrControlSecurityLogFileName.description: The name of the binary security log file.

acEventMgrControlSecurityLogFileWrapEnab.name: acEventMgrControlSecurityLogFileWrapEnable
acEventMgrControlSecurityLogFileWrapEnab.description: When set to true, tells the event log manager to wrap the security event log file when it has reached the maximum size. Oldest log entries are overwritten first when a wrap condition is reached.

acEventMgrControlRedirectTraceSlot1.name: acEventMgrControlRedirectTraceSlot1
acEventMgrControlRedirectTraceSlot1.description: When set to true, events that originate in slot 1 and would otherwise be displayed on the global standard output (console or telnet session) of slot 1, will instead be displayed on the global standard output of the master switch.

acEventMgrControlRedirectTraceSlot2.name: acEventMgrControlRedirectTraceSlot2
acEventMgrControlRedirectTraceSlot2.description: When set to true, events that originate in slot 2 and would otherwise be displayed on the global standard output (console or telnet session) of slot 2, will instead be displayed on the global standard output of the master switch.

acEventMgrAgentTable.name: acEventMgrAgentTable
acEventMgrAgentTable.description: This table provides configuration on a per agent basis for the handling of event messages from each agent. This table is automatically created by the system and does not need to be generated by the EMS.

acEventMgrAgentEntry.name: acEventMgrAgentEntry
acEventMgrAgentEntry.description: A row per entity which allows for configuration settings on how eventlog messages generated by this entity are stored and reported for the EMS.

acEventMgrAgentNodeId.name: acEventMgrAgentNodeId
acEventMgrAgentNodeId.description: A unique node identification number which uniquely identifies a node within an Appian ring of OSAPs.

acEventMgrAgentId.name: acEventMgrAgentId
acEventMgrAgentId.description: The acEventMgrAgentId identifies the agent which will be logging events within the event manager subsystem. The enumeration list of these well known ID's are published and used by the EMS in decoding the event log information for which agent has recorded an event.

acEventMgrAgentName.name: acEventMgrAgentName
acEventMgrAgentName.description: An ASCII name of the well known agent, sutible for display.

acEventMgrAgentAdminStatus.name: acEventMgrAgentAdminStatus
acEventMgrAgentAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acEventMgrAgentLogLevel.name: acEventMgrAgentLogLevel
acEventMgrAgentLogLevel.description: The logging level at which this entity will generate events destined for the event log manager. Currently this value is a bit mask allowing the user to select which types of events to store in the log. The bit mask values are selected as follows based on the position of the bit: critical(1), -- Critical means needs immediate attn. major(2), -- The resources may be exhausted soon. minor(4), -- Early indication of resource exhaustion. warning(8), -- Warnings, non-fatal. info(16), -- Informational event. debug(32), -- Used for debugging only. cleared(64), -- An alarm is being cleared. security-critical(128), -- Security log - Critical means needs immediate attn. security-major(256), -- Security log - The resources may be exhausted soon. security-minor(512), -- Security log - Early indication of resource exhaustion. security-warning(1024), -- Security log - Warnings, non-fatal. security-info(2048), -- Security log - Informational event. security-debug(4096), -- Security log - Used for debugging only. security-cleared(8192) -- Security log - An alarm is being cleared. The mask is generated as a logical OR of the values defined above.

acEventMgrAgentNumberEvents.name: acEventMgrAgentNumberEvents
acEventMgrAgentNumberEvents.description: The total number of events this entity has generated on this slot.

acEventMgrAgentLastEventCode.name: acEventMgrAgentLastEventCode
acEventMgrAgentLastEventCode.description: The last event ID which was generated by this entity on this slot.

acEventMgrAgentLastEventCount.name: acEventMgrAgentLastEventCount
acEventMgrAgentLastEventCount.description: The number of times the last event ID has been generated on this slot. Helpful in keeping a running count of the last event in the case of repeating errors.

acEventMgrAgentSlot.name: acEventMgrAgentSlot
acEventMgrAgentSlot.description: The slot number where the configuration of this row will be applied.

acEventMgrAgentTraceLevel.name: acEventMgrAgentTraceLevel
acEventMgrAgentTraceLevel.description: Specifies what types of events originated by this entity will be displayed on the standard global output as traces. Currently this value is a bit mask allowing the user to select which types of events to display. The bit mask values are selected as follows based on the position of the bit: critical(1), -- Critical means needs immediate attn. major(2), -- The resources may be exhausted soon. minor(4), -- Early indication of resource exhaustion. warning(8), -- Warnings, non-fatal. info(16), -- Informational event. debug(32), -- Used for debugging only. cleared(64), -- An alarm is being cleared. security-critical(128), -- Security log - Critical means needs immediate attn. security-major(256), -- Security log - The resources may be exhausted soon. security-minor(512), -- Security log - Early indication of resource exhaustion. security-warning(1024), -- Security log - Warnings, non-fatal. security-info(2048), -- Security log - Informational event. security-debug(4096), -- Security log - Used for debugging only. security-cleared(8192) -- Security log - An alarm is being cleared. The mask is generated as a logical OR of the values defined above.

acEventMgrLogFullTrap.name: acEventMgrLogFullTrap
acEventMgrLogFullTrap.description: The event log is over 90% full and wrapping is not enabled.

acEventMgrSecurityLogFullTrap.name: acEventMgrSecurityLogFullTrap
acEventMgrSecurityLogFullTrap.description: The security log is over 90% full and wrapping is not enabled.

acEventMgrLogFileCloseFailedTrap.name: acEventMgrLogFileCloseFailedTrap
acEventMgrLogFileCloseFailedTrap.description: The regular log file couldn't be closed.

acEventMgrSecurityLogFileCloseFailedTrap.name: acEventMgrSecurityLogFileCloseFailedTrap
acEventMgrSecurityLogFileCloseFailedTrap.description: The security log file couldn't be closed.

acConfigMgrTable.name: acConfigMgrTable
acConfigMgrTable.description: The configuration manager configuration parameters in a table which is indexed by a unique AcNodeId.

acConfigMgrEntry.name: acConfigMgrEntry
acConfigMgrEntry.description: Single record per node which contains the configuration parameters for the configuration manager agent. This row is automatically created by the agent upon system initialization.

acConfigMgrNodeId.name: acConfigMgrNodeId
acConfigMgrNodeId.description: A unique number assigned by the EMS which uniquely identifies a node within an Appian ring of OSAP's.

acConfigMgrAdminStatus.name: acConfigMgrAdminStatus
acConfigMgrAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acConfigMgrCurrentRevision.name: acConfigMgrCurrentRevision
acConfigMgrCurrentRevision.description: The numeric revision number for the configuration file. This number is Appian specific and not an RCS type revision for the file, but instead an internal software revision of the file format.

acConfigMgrFileName.name: acConfigMgrFileName
acConfigMgrFileName.description: The name of the configuration file. When the system boots, this config file is expected to be on the file system and will be the file that the system uses for normal operation.

acConfigMgrAutoSaveInterval.name: acConfigMgrAutoSaveInterval
acConfigMgrAutoSaveInterval.description: The number of seconds after a provisioning change when the config file is updated with the current state of configuration for this node. The acConfigMgrAutoSaveEnable flag must be set to true(1) for auto-save to take place.

acConfigMgrAutoSaveEnable.name: acConfigMgrAutoSaveEnable
acConfigMgrAutoSaveEnable.description: When set to true(1), the configuration manager will perform an update operation on the configuration file after 'n' seconds from the last provisioning change, specified by acConfigMgrAutoSaveInterval. Enabling this feature allows the EMS to assume the platform is in sync with a recent dynamic provisioning change, vs. sending down a new configuration file.

acConfigMgrLastWritten.name: acConfigMgrLastWritten
acConfigMgrLastWritten.description: The last time the configuration file was updated automatically.

acConfigMgrSaveConfig.name: acConfigMgrSaveConfig
acConfigMgrSaveConfig.description: When set to true(1), the configuration manager will perform an update operation on the configuration file immediately.

acConfigMgrOpStatus.name: acConfigMgrOpStatus
acConfigMgrOpStatus.description: This attribute indicates the configuration file save status when acConfigMgrSaveConfig is set.

acConfigMgrConfigFileCloseFailedTrap.name: acConfigMgrConfigFileCloseFailedTrap
acConfigMgrConfigFileCloseFailedTrap.description: The configuration file couldn't be closed.

acSntpMgrTable.name: acSntpMgrTable
acSntpMgrTable.description: The SNTP Manager is responsible for controlling the SNTP client agent on the SCP. The SNTP client will peer with a time server which itself may peer with a higher stratum clock or a radio receiver.

acSntpMgrEntry.name: acSntpMgrEntry
acSntpMgrEntry.description: A configuration record for the SNTP client agent.

acSntpMgrNodeId.name: acSntpMgrNodeId
acSntpMgrNodeId.description: A unique identifier assigned by the EMS which uniquely identifies a node within an Appian ring of OSAP's.

acSntpMgrAdminStatus.name: acSntpMgrAdminStatus
acSntpMgrAdminStatus.description: Attribute allowing enable/disabling control of the SNTP agent for provisioning changes. Refer to AcAdminStatus definition in appian-smi.mib.

acSntpMgrOpStatus.name: acSntpMgrOpStatus
acSntpMgrOpStatus.description: Attribute which describes the current operational status of the SNTP client agent. Refer to AcOpStatus definition in appian-smi.mib.

acSntpMgrErrorCode.name: acSntpMgrErrorCode
acSntpMgrErrorCode.description: If an error is reported in acSntpMgrOpStatus, this attribute will contain a detailed error code which can be referenced to determine the cause of a problem. The eventlog will also contain the failure reason.

acSntpMgrPeerIpAddress.name: acSntpMgrPeerIpAddress
acSntpMgrPeerIpAddress.description: The configured IP Address in dotted notation which SNTP uses to perform NTP queries against. The peer should be a Stratum-2 or greater clock.

acSntpMgrQueryInterval.name: acSntpMgrQueryInterval
acSntpMgrQueryInterval.description: The interval expressed in the number of seconds between NTP Query requests.

acSntpMgrRetryCount.name: acSntpMgrRetryCount
acSntpMgrRetryCount.description: The number of query attempts the SNTP client should perform before reporting that the SNTP client cannot communicate with the peer.

acSntpMgrMaxVariance.name: acSntpMgrMaxVariance
acSntpMgrMaxVariance.description: The variance expressed as the number of milliseconds between client and peer which will trigger an alarm. This is useful in determining if the historical data recorded in NOVRAM for statistics trending or timestamps used for traps is outside the configured variance parameter.

acSntpMgrVariance.name: acSntpMgrVariance
acSntpMgrVariance.description: The amount of time expressed as the number of milliseconds delta between client and peer.

acSntpMgrVarianceDetectEnable.name: acSntpMgrVarianceDetectEnable
acSntpMgrVarianceDetectEnable.description: Used to enable or disable variance threshold alarms.

acSntpMgrTimeZone.name: acSntpMgrTimeZone
acSntpMgrTimeZone.description: The time zone this node is currently located in, expressed as an integer ranging from 0 to 23, representing the 24 hr time- zones starting at UTC which is equal to 0 and proceeding in the positive westerly direction. ie: Boston = 5, California=8. Note: Daylight savings time is not automatically calculated.

acSntpMgrDayLightSaving.name: acSntpMgrDayLightSaving
acSntpMgrDayLightSaving.description: It specifies if daylight saving time is applicable.

acSntpMgrPeerFailureTrap.name: acSntpMgrPeerFailureTrap
acSntpMgrPeerFailureTrap.description: The SNTP Client is unable to communicate with the NTP Server which has been configured.

acSntpMgrVarianceTrap.name: acSntpMgrVarianceTrap
acSntpMgrVarianceTrap.description: The difference in time between client and peer exceeds the configured variance.

acSntpMgrHardwareTrap.name: acSntpMgrHardwareTrap
acSntpMgrHardwareTrap.description: The SNTP Client was unable to read or write the hardware clock.

acAuthMgrTable.name: acAuthMgrTable
acAuthMgrTable.description: The Authentication Manager is responsible for tracking who is logged into the system and how many success or failure events have occured for a unique user. As users log off the system they will be removed from the table.

acAuthMgrEntry.name: acAuthMgrEntry
acAuthMgrEntry.description: A single row within the authentication table tracking a single user session which can be via telnet, serial, rlogin or ftp.

acAuthMgrNodeId.name: acAuthMgrNodeId
acAuthMgrNodeId.description: A unique number within an Appian Ring identifying the node for which the user is logged into.

acAuthMgrUserId.name: acAuthMgrUserId
acAuthMgrUserId.description: A unique identifier within an Appian node which is used to identify the user currently attempting to gain access to the system.

acAuthMgrUserName.name: acAuthMgrUserName
acAuthMgrUserName.description: A unique identifier within an Appian node which is used to identify the user currently attempting to gain access to the system.

acAuthMgrAccessMode.name: acAuthMgrAccessMode
acAuthMgrAccessMode.description: The current access method for this user.

acAuthMgrLogonTime.name: acAuthMgrLogonTime
acAuthMgrLogonTime.description: The logon time this user was given access.

acAuthMgrFailures.name: acAuthMgrFailures
acAuthMgrFailures.description: The total number of logon attempts for a user who was given access to the system and who is currently still logged in, or the failure attempts for a user who attempted to gain access but did not.

acAuthMgrLockOut.name: acAuthMgrLockOut
acAuthMgrLockOut.description: This field will read true(1) when the max number of failures has been reached for an attempted logon using the user name listed in this row.

acAuthMgrDeleteEntry.name: acAuthMgrDeleteEntry
acAuthMgrDeleteEntry.description: Used to delete rows in this table.

acTrapMgrDestAddrTable.name: acTrapMgrDestAddrTable
acTrapMgrDestAddrTable.description: Table that specifies trap destination IP addresses for the different communities.

acTrapMgrDestAddrEntry.name: acTrapMgrDestAddrEntry
acTrapMgrDestAddrEntry.description: Entry that specifies, for a given community, an IP address to send traps to.

acTrapMgrDestAddrNodeId.name: acTrapMgrDestAddrNodeId
acTrapMgrDestAddrNodeId.description: Unique identification number of this node within an Appian ring.

acTrapMgrDestAddrCommId.name: acTrapMgrDestAddrCommId
acTrapMgrDestAddrCommId.description: Number that uniquely identifies a community.

acTrapMgrDestAddrIpAddress.name: acTrapMgrDestAddrIpAddress
acTrapMgrDestAddrIpAddress.description: IP address to send traps to.

acTrapMgrDestAddrAdminStatus.name: acTrapMgrDestAddrAdminStatus
acTrapMgrDestAddrAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acTrapMgrFilterTable.name: acTrapMgrFilterTable
acTrapMgrFilterTable.description: Table that lists, for the different communities, the traps that these communities don't want to receive.

acTrapMgrFilterEntry.name: acTrapMgrFilterEntry
acTrapMgrFilterEntry.description: This entry specifies a trap type (by OID) that the specified community is not interested in receiving.

acTrapMgrFilterNodeId.name: acTrapMgrFilterNodeId
acTrapMgrFilterNodeId.description: Unique identification number of this node within an Appian ring.

acTrapMgrFilterCommId.name: acTrapMgrFilterCommId
acTrapMgrFilterCommId.description: Number that uniquely identifies a community.

acTrapMgrFilterId.name: acTrapMgrFilterId
acTrapMgrFilterId.description: Number that, for the given node and community, uniquely identifies this filter.

acTrapMgrFilterAdminStatus.name: acTrapMgrFilterAdminStatus
acTrapMgrFilterAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acTrapMgrFilterTrapOid.name: acTrapMgrFilterTrapOid
acTrapMgrFilterTrapOid.description: Object identifier that identifies the trap type that will not be sent to the given community.

acTrapMgrResendTable.name: acTrapMgrResendTable
acTrapMgrResendTable.description: Table that allows a management system to request traps to be resent. Only the last 100 traps generated by the OSAP will be stored.

acTrapMgrResendEntry.name: acTrapMgrResendEntry
acTrapMgrResendEntry.description: Setting this entry triggers the specified traps to be resent to the destination IP address specified.

acTrapMgrResendNodeId.name: acTrapMgrResendNodeId
acTrapMgrResendNodeId.description: Unique identification number of this node within an Appian ring.

acTrapMgrResendAdminStatus.name: acTrapMgrResendAdminStatus
acTrapMgrResendAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acTrapMgrResendFromSeqId.name: acTrapMgrResendFromSeqId
acTrapMgrResendFromSeqId.description: Beginning of trap sequence number interval of traps to resend.

acTrapMgrResendToSeqId.name: acTrapMgrResendToSeqId
acTrapMgrResendToSeqId.description: End of trap sequence number interval of traps to resend. If acTrapMgrResendToSeqId is the same as acTrapMgrResendFromSeqId, then only 1 trap is sent.

acAuthenticationFailureTrap.name: acAuthenticationFailureTrap
acAuthenticationFailureTrap.description: Access denied due to a Logon Authentication failure.

acAuthenticationExceededTrap.name: acAuthenticationExceededTrap
acAuthenticationExceededTrap.description: The maximum number of authentication failure attempts has been exceeded. Access has been denied.

acFileXferMgrTable.name: acFileXferMgrTable
acFileXferMgrTable.description: This table contains file transfer operation information. This table is created during the initialization of the system. The EMS does not create new rows in it.

acFileXferMgrEntry.name: acFileXferMgrEntry
acFileXferMgrEntry.description: Each row in this table indicates a file transfer operation.

acFileXferMgrNodeId.name: acFileXferMgrNodeId
acFileXferMgrNodeId.description: A unique node identification number which uniquely identifies a node within an Appian ring of OSAPs.

acFileXferMgrRowId.name: acFileXferMgrRowId
acFileXferMgrRowId.description: The acFileXferMgrRowId identifies the row index of the table.

acFileXferMgrAdminStatus.name: acFileXferMgrAdminStatus
acFileXferMgrAdminStatus.description: The administrative status. See AcAdminStatus for the semantics.

acFileXferMgrOperation.name: acFileXferMgrOperation
acFileXferMgrOperation.description: The operation type. The upload and download indicate the direction of the file transfer from the perspective of the OSAP. A download is an ftp get from the ftp server, and an upload is an ftp put to the ftp server.

acFileXferMgrFiletype.name: acFileXferMgrFiletype
acFileXferMgrFiletype.description: This attribute indicates whether a binary image, or a binary event log, a textual configuration file or any other file is being transferred.

acFileXferMgrFilesubtype.name: acFileXferMgrFilesubtype
acFileXferMgrFilesubtype.description: This attribute indicates what type of file it is.

acFileXferMgrFtpServerIpAddress.name: acFileXferMgrFtpServerIpAddress
acFileXferMgrFtpServerIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the ftp server from where the file is being transferred.

acFileXferMgrUsername.name: acFileXferMgrUsername
acFileXferMgrUsername.description: The user name to be used for the ftp login authentication. This is optional. If not supplied, the default value is used.

acFileXferMgrPassword.name: acFileXferMgrPassword
acFileXferMgrPassword.description: The password to be used for the ftp login authentication. This is optional. If not supplied, the default value is used, which is the chassis name of the OSAP. When supplied, the password is in the clear-text form.

acFileXferMgrSourceDirectory.name: acFileXferMgrSourceDirectory
acFileXferMgrSourceDirectory.description: The name of the source directory for the file transfer operation.

acFileXferMgrSourceFilename.name: acFileXferMgrSourceFilename
acFileXferMgrSourceFilename.description: The name of the source file for the file transfer operation.

acFileXferMgrDestDirectory.name: acFileXferMgrDestDirectory
acFileXferMgrDestDirectory.description: The name of the destination directory for the file transfer operation.

acFileXferMgrDestFilename.name: acFileXferMgrDestFilename
acFileXferMgrDestFilename.description: The name of the destination file for the file transfer operation.

acFileXferMgrXferMode.name: acFileXferMgrXferMode
acFileXferMgrXferMode.description: This attribute indicates the mode of the transfer: ascii or binary.

acFileXferMgrOpStatus.name: acFileXferMgrOpStatus
acFileXferMgrOpStatus.description: This attribute indicates whether the file transfer operation has been successful, or failed, or in progress.

acRdpMgrTable.name: acRdpMgrTable
acRdpMgrTable.description: This table contains general Appian ring information discovered through the Ring Discovery Protocol (RDP).

acRdpMgrEntry.name: acRdpMgrEntry
acRdpMgrEntry.description: General Appian ring information discovered through RDP by the node specified by the index acRdpMgrNodeId.

acRdpMgrNodeId.name: acRdpMgrNodeId
acRdpMgrNodeId.description: Identifies the node where the Appian ring information was gathered.

acRdpMgrFsmState.name: acRdpMgrFsmState
acRdpMgrFsmState.description: State of the RDP Finite State Machine. Possible values: - isolated: the node is isolated. - discovery: the node is not isolated and is in the process of gathering Appian ring information. - master: the Appian ring information has been gathered and this node plays the role of master in the Ring Discovery Protocol (node with lowest Appian DCC MAC in the ring). - pleb: the Appian ring information has been gathered and this node does not play the role of master in the Ring Discovery Protocol (there is a node with a lower Appian DCC MAC in the ring).

acRdpMgrRingMasterNodeMac.name: acRdpMgrRingMasterNodeMac
acRdpMgrRingMasterNodeMac.description: MAC address of RDP master node in the Appian ring.

acRdpMgrRingTopology.name: acRdpMgrRingTopology
acRdpMgrRingTopology.description: Appian ring topology. Possible values: - unknown: there is not enough information available to determine whether this node is part of an open or closed ring. - open: two of the nodes in the ring are configured as End Systems. - closed: all nodes in the ring are configured as Intermediate Systems.

acRdpMgrRingState.name: acRdpMgrRingState
acRdpMgrRingState.description: Appian ring state: - unknown: there is not enough information available to determine whether the Appian ring is complete or incomplete. - complete: the ring map obtained contains all nodes in the ring. - incomplete: the ring map obtained does not contain all nodes in the ring. This may be due to a broken optical link or to misconfiguration of any of the nodes in the ring (wrong acChassisNodeArchitecture).

acRdpMgrRingSize.name: acRdpMgrRingSize
acRdpMgrRingSize.description: Number of nodes in the Appian ring. The special value -1 means the ring size is unknown.

acRdpMgrRdpVersion.name: acRdpMgrRdpVersion
acRdpMgrRdpVersion.description: Current version of the Ring Discovery Protocol (RDP)

acRdpMgrNodeTable.name: acRdpMgrNodeTable
acRdpMgrNodeTable.description: This table contains information about the different nodes in the Appian DCC ring that this node is part of. The first entry in this table corresponds to this node. Each entry in the table corresponds to the East neighbor of the node referred to by the previous entry.

acRdpMgrNodeEntry.name: acRdpMgrNodeEntry
acRdpMgrNodeEntry.description: Each row in this table contains information about a node in the Appian DCC ring.

acRdpMgrNodeThisNodeId.name: acRdpMgrNodeThisNodeId
acRdpMgrNodeThisNodeId.description: A unique node identification number which uniquely identifies this node within an Appian ring of OSAPs.

acRdpMgrNodeRowId.name: acRdpMgrNodeRowId
acRdpMgrNodeRowId.description: Index that identifies this row in the table.

acRdpMgrNodeNodeId.name: acRdpMgrNodeNodeId
acRdpMgrNodeNodeId.description: Node Id of node represented by this entry in the table.

acRdpMgrNodeADccIpAddress.name: acRdpMgrNodeADccIpAddress
acRdpMgrNodeADccIpAddress.description: IP address assigned to the Appian DCC management access interface of the node represented by this entry in the table.

acRdpMgrNodeADccMacAddress.name: acRdpMgrNodeADccMacAddress
acRdpMgrNodeADccMacAddress.description: Appian DCC MAC address of the node represented by this entry in the table.

acRdpMgrNodeADccConfig.name: acRdpMgrNodeADccConfig
acRdpMgrNodeADccConfig.description: RDP node configuration. Possible values: - unknown: the node configuration is unknown. - is: Intermediate System. The node is expected to have both an East and a West neighbor node in the Appian DCC ring. - ese: End System East. The node is expected to only have a West neighbor node in the Appian DCC ring. - esw: End System West. The node is expected to only have an East neighbor node in the Appian DCC ring.

acRdpMgrNodeADccEastOk.name: acRdpMgrNodeADccEastOk
acRdpMgrNodeADccEastOk.description: Specifies whether RDP is active (there is light and we are receiving RDP packets) on the East interface.

acRdpMgrNodeADccWestOk.name: acRdpMgrNodeADccWestOk
acRdpMgrNodeADccWestOk.description: Specifies whether RDP is active (there is light and we are receiving RDP packets) on the West interface.

acRdpMgrRingMapChangedTrap.name: acRdpMgrRingMapChangedTrap
acRdpMgrRingMapChangedTrap.description: The ring map obtained by RDP has changed.

acRdpMgrDuplicateNodeIdTrap.name: acRdpMgrDuplicateNodeIdTrap
acRdpMgrDuplicateNodeIdTrap.description: There are two nodes in the ring with the same node Id.
